title: Ground News - Fatal Pedestrian Crash on Gandy Boulevard Under Investigation by Florida Highway Patrol
text:
Summary by IONTB The Florida Highway Patrol (FHP) is actively investigating a fatal pedestrian crash that occurred on Gandy Boulevard on December 27, 2023 at approximately 10:30 p.m. The incident involved a Nissan Maxima traveling eastbound in the 13090 block of Gandy Boulevard. East of San Fernando Boulevard, a 58-year-old pedestrian from Hopatcong, New Jersey, attempted to cross Gandy Boulevard and was struck by the Maxima.
